## Event Hub configuration

The Event Hub connection string is stored securely in an Azure DevOps Library variable group.

Use this application-setting/environment-variable name unless the repository already has an agreed equivalent:

`EVENT_HUB_CONNECTION_STRING`

Do not hardcode any real connection string, key, namespace, or secret in source control.

Also support an optional Event Hub name setting:

`EVENT_HUB_NAME`

Use `EVENT_HUB_NAME` only when the connection string does not already contain `EntityPath`.

The implementation must support both cases:

1. Event Hub connection string contains `EntityPath`.
2. Namespace-level connection string is provided and the Event Hub entity name comes from `EVENT_HUB_NAME`.

